{{nihongo|'''Isoya Yoshida'''|吉田 五十八|Yoshida Isoya|[[December 19]], [[1894]], - [[March 24]], [[1974]]}} was a [[Japan]]ese [[architecture|architect]].  He graduated from Tokyo Art School (now [[Tokyo National University of Fine Arts and Music]]) in 1923.  His style, known as ''sukiya'', combines elements of traditional Japanese architecture and [[Modernism|modernist architecture]].  He was born and died in Tokyo.

